    client.iloc[i] = data.query('Churn == @i').mode().loc[0]
    client.iloc[i][['MonthlyCharges', 'TotalCharges', 'Duration']] = \
        data.query('Churn == @i')[['MonthlyCharges', 'TotalCharges', 'Duration']] \
        .median()
    client.iloc[i]['customerID'] = 'churn ' + str(i)

In [53]:
#  20%, 40%, 60%  80% 
quan = quantiles(data['TotalCharges'], n=5)

#   
def categorize_charges(charges):
    if charges <= quan[0]:
        return 'very low'
    if charges <= quan[1]:
        return 'low'
    if charges <= quan[2]:
        return 'medium'
    if charges <= quan[3]:
        return 'high'
    return 'very high'

#   'TotalChargesCategory'
data['TotalChargesCategory'] = data['TotalCharges'].apply(categorize_charges)
